This paper is about compositionality in language, which is a topic that falls under computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses different ways of representing phrases, such as vectors and language models, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed method involves using ranked lists of term weights, which is a technique commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and data analysis (cs.CC). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, and cs.CC, in that order.
